38. Interpret the steps to iterate over a PHP array using a while loop with an example
ANSWER
<?php
// Define an array
$fruits = array("Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango");
// Start iteration
while (($fruit = current($fruits)) !== false) {
    // Get current key (optional)
    $key = key($fruits);
// Print key and value
    echo "Key: $key, Value: $fruit<br>";
 // Move to the next element
    next($fruits);
}
?>

OUTPUT
Key: 0, Value: Apple
Key: 1, Value: Banana
Key: 2, Value: Cherry
Key: 3, Value: Mango
